cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach to self-attention, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and speech processing. The paper also introduces a new model that reduces the complexity of attention, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Finally, the model uses online k-means, which is a clustering algorithm, and this technique is commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
